# Testing Conventions

## Framework & Setup

- Vitest with jsdom environment ‚Äî globals enabled (no imports needed for describe/it/test)
- Setup file: `setupTests.ts` (canvas mock, FontFace, IndexedDB, matchMedia, clipboard polyfills)
- Canvas mocked via `vitest-canvas-mock` ‚Äî do NOT test actual pixel output
- Use `reseed(n)` for deterministic random IDs in tests

## Rendering Components

- Use custom `render()` from `packages/excalidraw/tests/test-utils.ts` ‚Äî NOT raw `@testing-library/react`
- Always `await render(<Excalidraw />)` ‚Äî it waits for canvas initialization
- Clean up with `unmountComponent()` in `beforeEach`
- Access state via `GlobalTestState.canvas`, `GlobalTestState.interactiveCanvas`

## Creating Elements

- Use `API.createElement({ type, x, y, width, height, ... })` from `tests/helpers/api.ts`
- Specialized helpers: `API.createTextContainer()`, `API.createLabeledArrow()`
- Set scene: `API.setElements([...])`, `API.setSelectedElements([...])`
- Update state: `API.setAppState(...)`, `API.updateScene(...)`

## Simulating User Input

- Mouse/touch: `new Pointer("mouse")` / `new Pointer("touch", id)` from `tests/helpers/ui.ts`
  - Relative: `mouse.move(dx, dy)`, `mouse.down()`, `mouse.up()`, `mouse.click()`
  - Absolute: `mouse.moveTo(x, y)`, `mouse.clickAt(x, y)`, `mouse.clickOn(element)`
- Keyboard: `Keyboard.keyPress(key)`, `Keyboard.undo()`, `Keyboard.redo()`
  - Modifiers: `Keyboard.withModifierKeys({ shift: true }, () => { ... })`
- Tools: `UI.clickTool("rectangle")`, `UI.createElement("rectangle", { position, size })`

## Assertions

- `assertSelectedElements(id1, id2)` or `assertSelectedElements([el1, el2])`
- `assertElements(actual, [{ type, x, y, selected: true }])` for structural comparison
- `checkpointHistory(h.history, "label")` for undo/redo stack snapshots
- Custom matcher: `expect(val).toBeNonNaNNumber()`

## Mocking & Spying

- Spy on renderers: `vi.spyOn(StaticScene, "renderStaticScene")`
- Mock modules: `vi.mock("@excalidraw/common", async (importOriginal) => ...)`
- Mock canvas dimensions: `mockBoundingClientRect({ width, height, x, y })`
- Mock images: `mockHTMLImageElement(width, height)`
- Clear mocks in `beforeEach`, NOT globally

## Snapshots

- Used extensively for render call counts, appState, elements, and history
- Snapshot precision: IEEE754 floats serialized to 5 decimal places
- Update with `yarn test:update`

## Test Commands

- `yarn test` ‚Äî run all tests
- `yarn test:coverage` ‚Äî run with coverage (thresholds: 60% lines, 70% branches, 63% functions)
- `yarn test:ui` ‚Äî Vitest UI dashboard
- `yarn test:update` ‚Äî update snapshots

## How to verify

- `yarn test:app --watch=false` ‚Äî all tests pass
- `yarn test:coverage` ‚Äî coverage meets thresholds (60% lines, 70% branches, 63% functions)
- `grep -rn "from '@testing-library/react'" packages/excalidraw/tests/` ‚Äî should only appear in test-utils.ts, not in individual tests
- `grep -rn "render(<" packages/excalidraw/tests/ | grep -v test-utils | grep -v "from.*test-utils"` ‚Äî verify tests use the custom render
- `git diff --name-only | grep "\.test\."` ‚Äî confirm changed code has corresponding test updates
